article.headline: Albany, N.Y. 26, Sacred Heart 21
article.story: FAIRFIELD, Conn. (A.P.) -David McCarty rushed for 207 yards and one touchdown to lead Albany over Sacred Heart 26-21 Saturday before 3,369 fans at Campus Field. The Great Danes (4-3, 3-0 Northeast Conference) rolled up 320 yards on the ground, including 217 in the second half, to erase a halftime deficit and hand the Pioneers (6-1, 2-1) their first loss of the season. An eight-yard touchdown pass from Dale Fink to Jared Kemp gave SHU a 14-10 lead with 4:39 left in the opening half, but the Great Danes would take over after the break with their speed option offense. Albany opened the third quarter with a 14-play, 80-yard drive, which McCarthy capped off with a 2-yard TD run, to take the lead for good at 17-14 with 9:52 left in the quarter. In the third quarter, Albany ran 28 offensive plays to SHU's five and consumed over 11 minutes on its two drives. On the second drive of the half, the Great Danes extended their lead to 20-14, at 14:55 of the fourth quarter, on a 34-yard field goal from Herb Glass. The kick completed a 16-play, 75-yard drive that consumed 6:38. Albany quarterback Vinny Esposito added an 18-yard touchdown run at 10:18 to give his team a 26-14 lead, but the two-point conversion attempt failed. Sacred Heart's Fink threw his second touchdown of the game -- connecting with Steve Tedesco on a 19-yard strike -- to pull SHU within 26-21 with 4:40 to play.
